        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 6. Shells of Scutellastra mexicana (left) and Lottia discors (right). (a) Dorsal view. (b) Ventral view. Scale bar: 4 cms." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5020894/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020888>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 3. Small specimen BR21. (a) Dorsal view of the shell of the small specimen. (b) Ventral view of the shell of the small specimen. (c) Ventral view of the soft tissue parts showing a diagnostic feature of small specimens, i.e. a ‘scalloped’ edge of the mantle. Scale bar: 5 cms." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5020888/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020892>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 5. (a) SEM photograph of a radula. Scale bar: 1 mm. (b) Detail of the pluricuspid lateral tooth (black arrow) and marginal teeth (white arrows). Scale bar:400 µm. (c) Optical microscope photograph of the radula. Scale bar: 1 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5020892/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5020886>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. Three different views of the same shell of Scutellastra mexicana (A, B, and C) recently found on beaches from the type locality Mazatlán. Scale bar: 10 cms." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5020886/files/figure.png" .

